**/node_modules/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
.env
.env.local
.env.*
!.env.example
.venv/
venv/
*.egg-info/
.pytest_cache/
# `.claude/` holds two kinds of content: tracked agent automation (hooks +
# settings — ships with the repo so every contributor's Claude Code session
# injects the AGENTS.md rules digest at startup) and transient session
# state (worktrees, cache, etc.) that must NOT be tracked. We ignore the
# contents by default and re-include only the tracked paths.
#
# NOTE: we deliberately ignore `.claude/*` (children) rather than `.claude/`
# (the directory itself). Once a directory is excluded via `dir/`, git
# cannot re-include children even with `!` rules — see gitignore(5).
.claude/*
!.claude/hooks/
!.claude/hooks/**
!.claude/settings.json
!.claude/skills/
!.claude/skills/**

# Agent/session artifacts
# Note: top-level CLAUDE.md is a tracked pointer file to AGENTS.md (the canonical
# contract). Session/scratch CLAUDE notes belong elsewhere (under docs/ or in
# .claude/). Do NOT re-ignore CLAUDE.md without also updating AGENTS.md guidance.
docs/ADMIN_CLAUDE_CODE_SESSIONS.md
docs/CLAUDE_CODE_SESSIONS*.md
docs/SESSION_*.md
docs/DECISION*.md
docs/MEMORY.md
docs/auto-memory/
docs/REPLAN_*.md
docs/REVISION_DIFF.md
docs/PREFLIGHT_REPORT.md
docs/CONSISTENCY_REPORT_*.md
docs/COVERAGE_GAP.json
docs/CI_BASELINE_ZERO.md

# Logs
*.log
logs/
npm-debug.log*

